President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals for posts at the Department of Treasury: Helen Elizabeth Garrett as Assistant Secretary for Tax Policy, Michael S. Barr as Assistant Secretary for Financial Institutions, and George W. Madison as General Counsel. President Obama expressed confidence in their expertise and commitment to tackle the nation's economic challenges. Helen Elizabeth Garrett is currently vice president for academic planning and budget at USC, while Michael S. Barr is a professor and Senior Fellow at the Center for American Progress and the Brookings Institution. George W. Madison is the former Executive Vice President and General Counsel of TIAA-CREF.